INSERT INTO "Pages" VALUES (124, 'Family Experiences', 'http://apps.visitnsw.com/smartphoneapps/south-coast/things-to-do/family-experiences', 1410486612000, '164,165,166,167,168', '{"Page":{"Title":"Family Experiences","Content":"\r\n<div id=\"content_div_195301\">\r\n<p>The South Coast has all the essential ingredients to be the perfect playground for a family holiday; sheltered beaches, parks to run around in, colourful birds to see and even kangaroos at the beach. There are plenty of ways to enjoy the great outdoors from finding sea shells to snorkelling, kayaking on lakes and rivers to fishing and dolphin-watch cruises. It\u2019s also a great place to introduce the kids to delicious local produce fresh from the farm at local cafes, farmers\u2019 markets or straight from the farmgate.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the best South Coast attractions are popular with kids of all ages. Top of the list of natural attractions is the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.visitnsw.com\/destinations\/south-coast\/kiama-area\/kiama\/attractions\/kiama-blowhole\">Kiama blowhole<\/a> with its spout of water that shoots up into the air with a \u201cwhoosh\u201d. The <a href=\"http:\/\/www.visitnsw.com\/destinations\/south-coast\/kiama-area\/jamberoo\/attractions\/illawarra-fly-treetop-walk\">Illawarra Fly Treetop Walk<\/a> has panoramic views over rainforest, the lush Jamberoo Valley and out to the ocean while the boardwalks and walking tracks in Minnamurra Rainforest provide spectacular views of the canyon carved out by the Minnamurra River.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/www.visitnsw.com\/destinations\/south-coast\/batemans-bay-and-eurobodalla\/mogo\/attractions\/mogo-zoo\">Mogo Zoo<\/a>, south of Batemans Bay, is home to rare and endangered species from around the globe. You might be surprised - and the kids will be amazed - to see red pandas, otters, Syrian brown bears and snow leopards in this major regional zoo. Make sure you book in for one of the keeper talks and feeding sessions to gain an insight into the natural behaviours of these beautiful animals. A National Park-guided tour of Montague Island is also a must-do South Coast experience. In this haven for marine and animal life, off the coast from Narooma, you\u2019ll see sleek fur seals, little penguins, peregrine falcons and crested terns. At Jervis Bay, dolphin watching is an all-year activity while whale watching is a seasonal experience from June to July and September to November.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Family holidays should be about fun and relaxing by doing things together. Why not hire bikes and go cycling along the beachfront at Wollongong, go paddling in a canoe on the Kangaroo Valley River or hire a dinghy on one of the region\u2019s pristine lakes - Conjola or Durras - and try your hand at catching dinner.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n","Images":[{"Full Size":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/197352_1.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/styles\/medium\/public\/197352_1.jpg?itok=Z3bii97s","Alt":"Burrill Lake Beach fun at Burrill","Modified":"2014-08-06 16:08:18"},{"Full Size":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/197351_1.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/styles\/medium\/public\/197351_1.jpg?itok=ot8qMpgk","Alt":"Booderee National Park","Modified":"2014-08-06 16:08:18"},{"Full Size":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/197353_1.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/styles\/medium\/public\/197353_1.jpg?itok=O_Jdspto","Alt":"Kayaking with dolphins","Modified":"2014-08-06 16:08:18"},{"Full Size":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/197354_1.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/styles\/medium\/public\/197354_1.jpg?itok=VaTnS-gb","Alt":"Tiger at Mogo Zoo","Modified":"2014-08-06 16:08:18"},{"Full Size":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/197355_1.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/styles\/medium\/public\/197355_1.jpg?itok=vTVcFylr","Alt":"Whale watching from boat","Modified":"2014-08-06 16:08:18"}]},"Children":[{"Name":"Must Do Links","Url":"http:\/\/apps.visitnsw.com\/smartphoneapps\/south-coast\/things-to-do\/family-experiences\/must-do-links"},{"Name":"Don\u2019t Miss","Url":"http:\/\/apps.visitnsw.com\/smartphoneapps\/south-coast\/things-to-do\/family-experiences\/dont-miss"}]}');
