INSERT INTO "Pages" VALUES (126, 'Don''t Miss', 'http://apps.visitnsw.com/smartphoneapps/south-coast/things-to-do/family-experiences/dont-miss', 1410486612000, '', '{"Page":{"Title":"Don\u2019t Miss","Content":"\r\n<div id=\"content_div_201685\">\r\n[{&quot;Name&quot;:&quot;Bodalla Dairy Shed&quot;,&quot;Web Path&quot;:&quot;bodalla-dairy-shed&quot;},{&quot;Name&quot;:&quot;Illawarra Fly Treetop Walk&quot;,&quot;Web Path&quot;:&quot;illawarra-fly-treetop-walk&quot;},{&quot;Name&quot;:&quot;Mogo Zoo&quot;,&quot;Web Path&quot;:&quot;mogo-zoo&quot;},{&quot;Name&quot;:&quot;Kangaroo Valley Safaris&quot;,&quot;Web Path&quot;:&quot;kangaroo-valley-safaris&quot;},{&quot;Name&quot;:&quot;Macquarie Pass National Park&quot;,&quot;Web Path&quot;:&quot;macquarie-pass-national-park&quot;},{&quot;Name&quot;:&quot;Whale Watching Tours&quot;,&quot;Web Path&quot;:&quot;cat-balou-cruises&quot;},{&quot;Name&quot;:&quot;Bass Fishing&quot;,&quot;Web Path&quot;:&quot;djs-estuary-adventures-and-eco-tours&quot;},{&quot;Name&quot;:&quot;Illawarra Golf Complex&quot;,&quot;Web Path&quot;:&quot;illawarra-golf-complex&quot;},{&quot;Name&quot;:&quot;Jervis Bay Whale Watching&quot;,&quot;Web Path&quot;:&quot;jervis-bay-whales&quot;},{&quot;Name&quot;:&quot;Pebbly Beach&quot;,&quot;Web Path&quot;:&quot;pebbly-beach&quot;},{&quot;Name&quot;:&quot;Austinmer Beach&quot;,&quot;Web Path&quot;:&quot;austinmer-beach&quot;}]\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n"}}');
INSERT INTO "Pages" VALUES (127, 'Food & Wine', 'http://apps.visitnsw.com/smartphoneapps/south-coast/food-and-wine', 1410486614000, '169,170,171', '{"Page":{"Title":"Food & Wine","Content":"\r\n<div id=\"content_div_195012\">\r\n<p>In the past, beaches and the lush green countryside were the main reasons to visit the South Coast. Today, food and wine experiences are likely to be top of the must-do list with excellent cafes, restaurants and cellar doors located along the coast. The region has all the essential ingredients for exceptional produce that\u2019s grown in an environment cherished for its pristine quality both on land and in the sea.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Seafood is a regional speciality. Stand-out local seafood includes oysters, prawns, tuna and kingfish which you can buy direct from the boat at fishermen\u2019s co-ops or enjoy at local fish and chip shops. Many South Coast restaurants include local seafood on their menus \u2013 check out <a href=\"http:\/\/www.visitnsw.com\/destinations\/south-coast\/batemans-bay-and-eurobodalla\/batemans-bay\/restaurants\/on-the-pier\">On the Pier<\/a> at <a href=\"http:\/\/www.destinationnsw.com.au\/smartphoneapps\/south-coast\/local-areas\/batemans-bay-and-eurobodalla\/batemans-bay\">Batemans Bay<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.visitnsw.com\/destinations\/south-coast\/jervis-bay-and-shoalhaven\/mollymook\/attractions\/rick-stein-at-bannisters\">Rick Stein at Bannisters<\/a> in <a href=\"http:\/\/www.destinationnsw.com.au\/smartphoneapps\/south-coast\/local-areas\/jervis-bay-and-shoalhaven\/mollymook\">Mollymook<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.visitnsw.com\/destinations\/south-coast\/batemans-bay-and-eurobodalla\/moruya\/restaurants\/the-river-moruya\">The River Moruya<\/a> Zanzibar Caf\u00e9 at <a href=\"http:\/\/www.destinationnsw.com.au\/smartphoneapps\/south-coast\/local-areas\/merimbula-and-saphire-coast\/merimbula\">Merimbula<\/a>. South Coast oysters are simply sublime and you can sample them at any number of locations. Don\u2019t miss <a href=\"http:\/\/www.visitnsw.com\/destinations\/south-coast\/jervis-bay-and-shoalhaven\/culburra-beach\/attractions\/jim-wilds-oyster-service\">Jim Wild\u2019s Oyster Service<\/a> at Greenwell Point, the Ulladulla Oyster Bar, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.visitnsw.com\/destinations\/south-coast\/merimbula-and-sapphire-coast\/pambula\/restaurants\/wheelers-oyster-farm-seafood-restaurant\">Wheelers Oyster Farm and Restaurant<\/a>, and the Pearly Oyster Bar in Batemans Bay.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>The South Coast has a long history of dairy farming and, as a result, cheese-making is well established in many locales. Take advantage of the chance to sample hand-made cheese from the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.visitnsw.com\/destinations\/south-coast\/batemans-bay-and-eurobodalla\/bodalla\/restaurants\/bodalla-dairy-shed\">Bodalla Dairy Shed<\/a>, the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.visitnsw.com\/destinations\/south-coast\/batemans-bay-and-eurobodalla\/central-tilba\/attractions\/abc-cheese-factory\">ABC Cheese Factory<\/a> in <a href=\"http:\/\/www.destinationnsw.com.au\/smartphoneapps\/south-coast\/local-areas\/batemans-bay-and-eurobodalla\/central-tilba\">Central Tilba<\/a> and the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.visitnsw.com\/destinations\/south-coast\/merimbula-and-sapphire-coast\/bega\/attractions\/bega-cheese-heritage-centre\">Bega Cheese Heritage Centre<\/a>. Meet the cheese makers and learn about the process behind producing beautiful hand-made cheese.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>You\u2019ll also find plenty of top nosh at restaurants and cafes along the coast and in the hinterland. Local drives may even take you along a food and wine trail \u2013 the Tathra-Bermagui Road, for example, passes through beautiful scenery straight to beautiful oysters! The <a href=\"http:\/\/www.visitnsw.com\/destinations\/south-coast\/jervis-bay-and-shoalhaven\/surrounds\/attractions\/south-coast-harvest-experience-farm-gate-trail-shoalhaven\">South Coast Harvest Farmgate Trail<\/a> introduces visitors to the best of local produce from wines and cheese to chocolate and berries. Watch out for local specialities such as gelato from the Austi Beach Bar, smoked trout, salmon and eel from the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.visitnsw.com\/destinations\/south-coast\/merimbula-and-sapphire-coast\/eden\/attractions\/eden-smokehouse\">Eden Smokehouse<\/a>, Disaster Bay chillies and seriously good coffer from mister jones at Bermagui.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SOUTH COAST WINERIES<\/strong><\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>The region\u2019s premier wine -growing region is the Shoalhaven, which now has around 18 vineyards and 16 cellar doors as well as a thriving food scene in Berry, Gerroa, Nowra, Milton and Ulladulla. Why not dine amongst the vines at <a href=\"http:\/\/www.visitnsw.com\/destinations\/south-coast\/jervis-bay-and-shoalhaven\/berry\/attractions\/silos-estate-and-wileys-creek\">The Silos Restaurant<\/a> at Coolangatta Estate or Culpitt\u2019s Winery at Ulladulla?<\/p>\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n","Images":[{"Full Size":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/197310_1.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/styles\/medium\/public\/197310_1.jpg?itok=OpZvDPqY","Alt":"Cupitt\u2019s Winery","Modified":"2014-08-06 16:08:18"},{"Full Size":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/197311_1.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/styles\/medium\/public\/197311_1.jpg?itok=Kd4fhnmz","Alt":"Oyster Farm in Merimbula","Modified":"2014-08-06 16:08:18"},{"Full Size":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/197312_1.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/images2.visitnsw.com\/sites\/default\/files\/styles\/medium\/public\/197312_1.jpg?itok=X34rA1DF","Alt":"Waterside dining at Tuross Lake","Modified":"2014-08-06 16:08:18"}]},"Children":[{"Name":"Must Do Links","Url":"http:\/\/apps.visitnsw.com\/smartphoneapps\/south-coast\/food-and-wine\/must-do-links"},{"Name":"Don\u2019t Miss","Url":"http:\/\/apps.visitnsw.com\/smartphoneapps\/south-coast\/food-and-wine\/dont-miss"}]}');
